# Python Backend — Clean Architecture (Hexagonal)

Patrón obligatorio. Principios globales: `engineering-standards.mdc`.

## Capas (dependencias solo hacia adentro)

```
API (routes)  →  Application (services, orchestrator)  →  Domain
                              ↓
                    Infrastructure (repos, LLM, RAG, web)
```

| Capa | Carpeta | Responsabilidad |
|------|---------|-----------------|
| **API** | `api/routes/` | HTTP, validación input, status codes — **sin lógica de negocio** |
| **Application** | `services/`, `orchestrator/` | Casos de uso, pipeline LangGraph |
| **Domain** | `domain/` | Entidades, enums, `compute_signals()` — **sin I/O** |
| **Infrastructure** | `repositories/`, `infrastructure/` | MongoDB, Azure OpenAI, RAG, web search |
| **Core** | `core/` | config, deps, exceptions, logging |

## Estructura

```
backend/app/
├── api/routes/           # transactions, evaluations, hitl, audit, health
├── services/             # FraudService, HitlService
├── domain/
│   ├── models.py         # Transaction, Decision, EvaluationResult
│   └── signals.py        # compute_signals() — lógica pura
├── agents/               # BaseAgent + 8 agentes (SRP cada uno)
├── orchestrator/         # LangGraph — ensambla agentes, no lógica de dominio
├── repositories/         # MongoDB (interfaces + implementación)
├── infrastructure/
│   ├── llm/              # Azure OpenAI client
│   ├── rag/              # Chroma / AI Search
│   └── web_search/       # Tavily / mock
├── models/               # Pydantic schemas API (DTOs)
└── core/                 # config, deps, exceptions
```

## Reglas por capa

- **Routes**: delegar a `service`; nunca llamar LLM, MongoDB ni agentes directo
- **Services**: orquestar repos + `orchestrator.run()`; transacciones de negocio
- **Domain**: funciones puras testeables; sin imports de FastAPI/Motor/LangChain
- **Agents**: `async run(state) → state`; interfaz común `BaseAgent`
- **Repositories**: CRUD por colección; sin lógica de fraude
- **Infrastructure**: adapters intercambiables (mock en tests)
- **Comments**: English only (`#`, docstrings) — `engineering-standards.mdc`

## Flujo evaluate

```
POST /api/transactions/{id}/evaluate
  → route valida tx_id
  → FraudService.evaluate(tx_id)
      → repository carga tx + behavior
      → orchestrator.run(state)
      → persiste evaluation + audit_events
  → EvaluationResult (Pydantic)
```

## Stack

FastAPI, LangGraph, Motor/Beanie, Chroma/AI Search — ver `mongodb.mdc`, `multi-agent-architecture.mdc`.

